South Africa's Budget Surplus More Than Doubles in February on Tax Revenue

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-03-30T12:08:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/south-africa-s-budget-surplus-more-than-doubles-in-february-on-tax-revenue.html
South Africa  posted a budget
surplus of 7.9 billion rand in February, more than double the
3.04 billion rand recorded a year ago, the National Treasury
said.  Revenue climbed an annual 10 percent to 64.55 billion rand,
while expenditure rose 2 percent to 56.6 billion rand, the
Treasury said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  